msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:163
msgid ""
"If you wish to break when a particular function is entered, insert its name "
"here. In C just the name will do e.g. 'main' or 'myFoo'. For C++ class "
"methods, you need to do 'MyClass::myFoo'\n"
"\n"
"Alternatively you can enter a regular expression, and tick the checkbox "
"below. A breakpoint will then be set on all matching functions."
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:172
msgid "This is a regex"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:174
msgid ""
"If you wish to insert a breakpoint on several functions, you can tick this "
"box, then enter a suitable regular expression in the textctrl above."
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:178
msgid "Memory address:"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:184
msgid ""
"To break on a memory address, enter the address here.\n"
"e.g. 0x0a1b2c3d or 12345678"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:191
msgid "In file:"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:200
msgid ""
"If you've entered a line-number, its assumed to refer to the current file. "
"If it isn't, enter the correct filename here.\n"
"\n"
"For a function, a file is usually not required. However, if you have several "
"functions with the same name, in several different files (do people _really_ "
"do that?) and you want to break on only one of those, enter the correct "
"filename here."
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:222
msgid "write only"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:223
msgid "read only"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:224
msgid "read-write"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:225
msgid "Type of watchpoint:"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:226
msgid ""
"The usual type of watchpoint is 'write-only': that is, it's triggered "
"whenever the target is changed.\n"
"\n"
"Alternatively you can choose for it to trigger when the target is read from, "
"or either written to or read from."
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:231
msgid "Data to watch:"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:236
msgid ""
"Identify the data to be watched. It can be one of:\n"
"1) Any variable name e.g. 'foo'\n"
"2) A memory address, suitably cast e.g.*(int*)0x12345678 will watch an int-"
"sized block starting at this address.\n"
"Don't include spaces in the expression: gdb can't understand them.\n"
"3) A complex expression e.g. a*b + c/d'. The expression can use any "
"operators valid in the program's native language.\n"
"\n"
"NB. A watchpoint set on a local variable will automatically be removed when "
"the variable loses scope."
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:244
msgid "Conditional Breaks: Add any condition here"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:249
msgid ""
"You can add a condition to any breakpoint or watchpoint. The debugger will "
"then stop only if the condition is met.\n"
"The condition can be any simple or complex expression in your programming "
"language, providing it returns a bool. However any variables that you use "
"must be in scope.\n"
"If you've previously set a condition and no longer want it, just clear this "
"textctrl."
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:253
msgid "Command List: Add any command(s) here"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:258
msgid ""
"You can add a list of commands to any breakpoint or watchpoint. When the "
"breakpoint is hit and the program interrupted, those commands will be "
"executed.\n"
"For example, to print the value of the variable foo and then continue "
"running the program, enter:\n"
"\tprint foo\n"
"\tcont\n"
"If you've previously entered commands, and no longer want them, just clear "
"this textctrl."
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:272
msgid "Disable"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:274
msgid ""
"If you check this box, the breakpoint (or watchpoint) will still exist, but "
"it won't trigger. If you uncheck it in the future, the breakpoint will work "
"again."
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:278
msgid "Make temporary"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:280
msgid ""
"A temporary breakpoint (or watchpoint) is one that works only once. When "
"it's hit it behaves like any other, except that it's then deleted."
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:284
msgid "Ignore count:"
msgstr ""

#: build-release/LiteEditor/breakpointdlgbase.cpp:285
msgid ""
"Enter a count >0 to ignore this breakpoint (or watchpoint) for that number "
"of times. It then behaves as though it is disabled, except that every time "
"it would have triggered, the ignore count decrements.\n"
"When the count reaches zero, the breakpoint becomes active again."
msgstr ""

